# Frontend (`fe/`)

- **Stack**: Vite, React, TypeScript. Package root is `fe/` (see `fe/package.json`).
- Prefer existing UI patterns, Radix/shadcn-style components, and project scripts (`npm run dev`, `npm run full-check` from `fe/`).

## Mobile-first (default)

Treat **narrow / touch** layouts as the baseline; widen and add complexity only at larger breakpoints.

- **CSS / Tailwind**: Unprefixed classes are the mobile default. Use `sm:`, `md:`, `lg:` (and up) to _add_ or _change_ behavior for larger viewports — never assume desktop-first and strip down with `max-*` unless there is a strong reason.
- **Layout**: Stack and scroll on small screens first; side-by-side, sidebars, and dense grids are enhancements at `sm` / `md` / `lg` as the rest of the app does.
- **Interaction**: Prefer tap-friendly targets and spacing on the base styles; keyboard/mouse refinements can layer on larger breakpoints.
- When unsure, **design and implement the smallest viewport first**, then scale up.
